an, Wales, United Kingdom","Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"ABT 1320–":"circa 1320–Overleden","1320–Male":"1320–Overleden","1324–Female":"1324–Overleden","1342–Female":"1342–Overleden","1350–Male":"1350–Overleden","1354–Male":"1354–Overleden","1296–Male":"1296–Overleden","1300–Female":"1300–Overleden","1296":"1296","1350":"1350","ABT 1316":"circa 1316","Abt 1349":"circa 1349","Abt 1350":"circa 1350","1324":"1324","ABT 1320":"circa 1320","1300":"1300","Abt 1342":"circa 1342","ABT 1354":"circa 1354","1354":"1354","1342":"1342","1320":"1320","of Meifod,Montgomery,Wales":"Meifod, Montgomeryshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Montgomery,Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Machen,Glamorgan,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ABT 1320–":"about 1320–Deceased","1320–Male":"1320–Deceased","1324–Female":"1324–Deceased","1342–Female":"1342–Deceased","1350–Male":"1350–Deceased","1354–Male":"1354–Deceased","1296–Male":"1296–Deceased","1300–Female":"1300–Deceased","1296":"1296","1350":"1350","ABT 1316":"about 1316","Abt 1349":"about 1349","Abt 1350":"about 1350","1324":"1324","ABT 1320":"about 1320","1300":"1300","Abt 1342":"about 1342","ABT 1354":"about 1354","1354":"1354","1342":"1342","1320":"1320","of Meifod,Montgomery,Wales":"Meifod, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Montgomery,Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Machen,Glamorgan,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Gruffudd","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Welsh: traditional spelling of   Griffith  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Griffith","meanings":["Welsh (Carmarthenshire and western England): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Gruffudd</i>, Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, composed of the elements <i>grip</i>, of uncertain significance, + <i>iud</i> ‘chief, lord’."]}]},{"name":"Llwyd","type":"LAST","meanings":["Same as Lhuyd, q v."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Llywelyn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["(Welsh)  See  Llewelyn ."],"variants":[{"name":"Llewelyn","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Llywelyn ap Gruffudd Llwyd was born about 1320, in Meifod, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Gruffudd Llwyd ap Llywelyn Foelgrwn, was 26 and his mother, verch Adda, was 22. He married verch Adda about 1349, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter."},"et":{"ABT 1320–":"umbes 1320–Surnud","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1324–Female":"1324–Surnud","1342–Female":"1342–Surnud","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1354–Male":"1354–Surnud","1296–Male":"1296–Surnud","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1296":"1296","1350":"1350","ABT 1316":"umbes 1316","Abt 1349":"umbes 1349","Abt 1350":"umbes 1350","1324":"1324","ABT 1320":"umbes 1320","1300":"1300","Abt 1342":"umbes 1342","ABT 1354":"umbes 1354","1354":"1354","1342":"1342","1320":"1320","of Meifod,Montgomery,Wales":"Meifod, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Montgomery,Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Machen,Glamorgan,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1320–":"noin 1320–Kuollut","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1324–Female":"1324–Kuollut","1342–Female":"1342–Kuollut","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1354–Male":"1354–Kuollut","1296–Male":"1296–Kuollut","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1296":"12